1. 💾 PERSISTENCE (The Vault): 
   We use <fstream> to talk to "squad_vault.txt". This isn't just for show—it saves 
   your Diamonds, Max Streak, and Unlocks between runs. If you close the game and 
   reopen it, your progress stays. This turns a simple script into a real game.

2. 🧠 THE DATA ARCHITECTURE:
   Everything is built on "Parallel Arrays." The Teammate names, their 5 questions, 
   their Truths, and their Lies all share the same index [0-7]. When the RNG picks 
   Index 3, the game knows it's talking to Luke, uses Luke’s trivia, and checks 
   Luke’s specific answers.

3. 💢 MOOD & MOOD-FILTERING:
   We added a `mood[]` array. Every time a player gets a question wrong for a specific 
   teammate, that teammate's "Frustration" goes up. If it hits 3, they get locked out 
   of the randomizer. It forces the player to be careful and adds a "social" layer 
   to the mechanics.

4. 💎 THE DIAMOND ECONOMY:
   - Session Diamonds: Earned via correct answers + Combo Multipliers (talking to 
     the same person repeatedly builds "loyalty" rewards).
   - Permanent Diamonds: Saved to the vault to buy HP upgrades in the Professor's 
     Office before the mission starts.

5. 🎓 THE PROFESSOR (Boss & Redemption):
   The Professor acts as two different states:
   - Redemption: A fail-safe. If you lose a life, you get one chance to answer a 
     hard-coded Prof question to save yourself.
   - Boss Mode: If you're brave enough to hit a 10-streak, you enter "The Lecture." 
     You have to pass 3 questions in a row to win the massive 50-diamond jackpot.

6. 💊 SPECIALIST SYNERGY:
   If you hit 100% Mastery with Vanessa (The Nurse), the code flips a boolean 
   flag in the save file. This permanently grants the +1 Life "Nurse Passive" to 
   EVERY class you pick in the future. It’s our version of an "Achievement Unlock."

7. 🛠️ CLEAN LOGIC:
   We use normalize() to kill case-sensitivity (so "YES" = "yes") and clean() 
   to wipe the input buffer. This prevents the "ghost input" bug where the 
   program skips questions.
